    feat: orphan detection, ML-learned baselines, correlation engine, memory mesh tracking
    
    Orphan service detection:
      GET /api/component-health/orphans ΓÇö finds services that are alive
      (health check passes) but receive zero business calls in 24 hours.
      Distinguishes 'orphan' from 'idle' ΓÇö a real operational blind spot.
    
    ML-learned baselines:
      GET /api/component-health/learned-baselines ΓÇö analyzes 7 days of
      Genesis key timestamps per component to learn natural activity rhythm.
      Calculates avg/median/max/min intervals, peak hours, quiet hours.
      Returns recommended_interval_min to replace static config.
      Uses TimeSense.activity_patterns() for hourly/daily rhythm detection.
    
    Correlation engine:
      GET /api/component-health/correlate/{id} ΓÇö when a component is broken,
      walks the dependency graph upstream to find the root cause.
      - If upstream dependencies are also down ΓåÆ marks as leaf failure,
        suppresses alert, points to root cause
      - If downstream components are affected ΓåÆ identifies cascade count
      - If neither ΓåÆ isolated local issue
      Diagnosis is plain English for the Dev tab.
    
    Memory mesh Genesis tracking:
      - ingest_learning_experience() now emits genesis key (learning_complete)
        with trust_score, has_episode, experience_type
      - get_learning_suggestions() now emits genesis key (gap_identified)
        with gap_count, failure_count, top_topics
      - Both track via parent_key_id for provenance chain
    
